@32304     = ~Glyph of Warding
(Abjuration) 
Level: Clr 3, Helm 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special 
Saving Throw: Reflex half

A Glyph of Warding is a powerful inscription, magically drawn to prevent unauthorized or hostile creatures from passing, entering, or opening.  It can be used to guard a small bridge, to ward an entry, or as a trap on a chest or box.  Any creature violating the warded area sets off the glyph. It deals 1d8 electrical damage per two levels (max 5d8) to the victims, though they may make a Reflex save for half damage.~
@31305     = ~Hold Animal~
@32305     = ~Hold Animal
(Enchantment) 
Level: Drd 2, Rgr 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 20-foot radius
Saving Throw: Will negates 

This spell holds animals rigidly immobile. Animals with magical powers such as winter wolves do count as animals, as do some of the more animalistic monsters such as remorhazes. The effect is centered on a point selected by the caster, and 1-4 animals within 20 feet of the target point are affected. Those who succeed on their Will save are unaffected by the spell. Being held does not prevent the worsening of the subject's condition due to wounds, disease, or poison.~
@31308     = ~Remove Paralysis~
@32308     = ~Remove Paralysis
(Conjuration) 
Level: Clr 2, Pal 2
Range: Close
Duration: Permanent 
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 25' Radius
Saving Throw: None 

The caster can free creatures from the effects of any paralysis, stunning, or related magic (such as a ghoul touch, or a Hold Person spell).~
@31310     = ~Miscast Magic~
@32310     = ~Miscast Magic
(Enchantment) 
Level: Clr 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 20 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will negates

Any spell casting creature that is affected by this spell has its casting ability severely disabled.  When the creature attempts to cast a spell, it has an 50% chance of failure.  Creatures can make a Will save (with +8 DC) to avoid the effect.~
