When the caster evokes Flame Strike, a vertical column of fire blasts downward into the area of effect.  All creatures caught in the area of effect take 1d6 damage per caster level (maximum 15d6). Half the damage is fire damage while the other half is holy fire damage, which ignores fire resistance. A successful Reflex save halves both kinds of damage.~
@31508     = ~Chaotic Commands~
@32508     = ~Chaotic Commands
(Enchantment) [Chaos]
Level: Clr 5, Tempus 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 10 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Chaotic Commands renders a creature immune to magical commands. Charm, Dominate Person, Command, Sleep, Fear, Stun, Confusion, Feeblemind, Hopelessness, and Symbol spells all fit into this category.~
@31523     = ~Static Charge~
@32523     = ~Static Charge
(Transmutation)
Level: Drd 5, Rgr 6, Talos 4
Duration: 5 turns
Casting Time: 1 round
Area of Effect: Sight of Caster
Saving Throw: Reflex half

Static Charge is similar to Call Lightning except it can be used indoors. Upon completion of this spell an enemy creature within the area of effect is fried by a static discharge for 1d8 electricity damage per caster level, to a maximum of 16d8 electricity damage. A successful Reflex save with +4 DC halves the damage. Once released the static charge will build up again on the caster, discharging once per 5 rounds for the duration of the spell.~
@31602     = ~Summon Nature's Ally VI~
