@32608    = ~Sol's Searing Orb
(Evocation)
Level: Clr 6, Drd 5, Rgr 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex half

Upon completion of this spell the caster hurls a brilliant, blazing sphere at a target creature. When it hits it explodes in a flash of light, blinding the target creature and dealing 9d12 points of fire damage. A successful Reflex save avoids the blindness and halves the damage. Drow and gray dwarves must make their Reflex save against blindness with +4 DC. Undead creatures are particularly vulnerable to this spell and take double damage.~
@31616     = ~Dolorous Decay~
@32616     = ~Dolorous Decay
(Necromancy) 
Level: Clr 6, Drd 6
Range: Sight of Caster 
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature 
Saving Throw: Fortitude negates

Dolorous decay is a rotting and withering of the body that spreads quickly and painfully throughout the afflicted creature.  Afflicted creatures take 1 point of damage per second and are slowed for 1 round per level.  The target creature can resist the disease with a successful Fortitude save at +8 DC.~
@31727     = ~Contagious Fear~
@32727     = ~Contagious Fear
(Necromancy)
Level: Brd 7, Clr 8, Sor/Wiz 8
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 10 rounds
Casting Time: 8
Area of Effect: 30-foot radius
Saving Throw: Will negates

Contagious Fear causes panic among enemies in the area of effect, and the panic then spreads to other creatures. Each enemy in the initial area of effect must make a Will save or run in fear for 10 rounds. Any enemy that comes within 10 feet of one of the panicking creatures must make the save as well, or else the contagion will spread to that creature. Creatures immune to fear will not transmit the contagion. A creature that makes a save against this spell is immune to the spell for 2 rounds. After the spell expires on a creature, that creature is immune to the contagion for 8 hours.~
