Level: Rgr 6
Range: Caster
Duration: 1 second/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell drastically speeds up the ranger's attack speed. For the duration, the ranger attacks twice as many times per round. Attack bonuses will continue to decrease for attacks beyond the 5th one.

Although rangers normally cast spells at half their caster level, Supreme Speed will be cast at a ranger's full caster level.~
@35657     = ~Explosive Smite~
@36657     = ~Explosive Smite
(Evocation)
Level: Pal 6
Range: Caster
Duration: 2 rounds or until triggered
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows the paladin to apply their Smite Evil as an area of effect. Casting Explosive Smite automatically causes the paladin to ready Smite Evil without consuming a use of it. The paladin gains their Charisma bonus to their next attack roll, and their next successful attack generates an explosion. All evil creatures within 20 feet take damage equal to the paladin's regular Smite Evil damage (though only the creature that was hit by the actual attack takes the attack's damage).~
@35658     = ~Trial by Fire~
@36658     = ~Trial by Fire
(Evocation)
Level: Clr 6, Pal 6
Range: Caster
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 20-foot long, 5-foot wide wall
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a wall of holy fire, which does not burn the innocent. Any non-good creature that passes through the wall takes 12d6 holy fire damage (which ignores fire resistance) with no Saving Throw. Good creatures can pass through the wall unharmed. Only one such wall can be active at a time.~
@35659     = ~Mass Heal Animal~
@36659     = ~Mass Heal Animal
(Conjuration)
Level: Drd 6, Rgr 6
Range: Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Allied animals within 20 ft.
Saving Throw: None

Mass Heal Animal wipes away disease and injury from all animals in the area of effect. It cures blindness, diseases, feeblemind and restores the targets to maximum hit points if they have been injured.~
@35660     = ~Desecrate~
@36660     = ~Desecrate
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 6
Range: Entire area
Duration: 8 hours
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: All undead in the area
Saving Throw: None

This spell imbues the current area with negative energy. For the duration, all undead gain +2 Constitution, get +2 to attack and damage, and count as 3 levels higher for purposes of resisting Turn Undead. In addition, any spell which would animate undead will create twice as many undead creatures when cast in the desecrated area. Desecrate can only be cast by evil characters.~
@35753     = ~Power Word: Heal~
@36753     = ~Power Word: Heal
(Divination)
Level: Brd 8, Clr 7
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Power Word: Heal is one of the beneficial words of power. When uttered, it heals a creature to their maximum hit points and cures poison, disease, blindness, deafness, feeblemindedness, intoxication, and bleeding. Power Word: Heal has no effect on undead.~
@35754     = ~Regeneration~
@36754     = ~Regeneration
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 7, Drd 8
Range: Touch
Duration: 1 round / 2 levels
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell lets a creature regenerate wounds very rapidly. For the duration, the target regenerates 3 HP per second.~
@35853     = ~Unholy Aura~
@36853     = ~Unholy Aura
(Abjuration)
Level: Clr 8
Range: 20 ft.
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Allies in a 20' radius
Saving Throw: None

A malevolent darkness surrounds the subjects, protecting them from attacks, granting them resistance to spells, and blinding good creatures when they strike the subjects. This abjuration has four effects:
First, the warded creatures gain a +4 deflection bonus to AC and a +4 bonus to all saves.
Second, the warded creature gains +10 spell resistance and 5/- resistance to all forms of magical damage.
Third, the abjuration protects the creatures against charm and domination spells.
Fourth, any creature of good alignment who strikes (melee only) those protected by the Unholy Aura must make a Fortitude save or be blinded for 3 round.
Unholy Aura can only be cast by evil characters.~
@35951     = ~Auril's Blessing~
@36951     = ~Auril's Blessing
(Conjuration)
Level: Drd 9
Range: Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell calls upon the power of Auril to amplify the caster's cold spells. For the duration, cold damage dealt by the caster is increased by 50%, or by 100% if cast at level 30 or higher. In addition, the spell Cone of Cold has +4 DC and a much larger area of effect, as does the Winter Wolf shapeshift form's cold breath.~
@35952     = ~Mass Harm~
@36952     = ~Mass Harm
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 9
Range: Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: All enemies within 30 ft.
Saving Throw: Fortitude negates

Mass Harm releases destructive negative energy upon all living enemies in the area of effect. The caster makes ranged touch attacks against each of those creatures; each one that get hit must Save vs. Fortitude or lose all but one hit point. The DC is the same as that of the 6th-level Harm spell. Allied undead in the area of effect are instead healed to full health as per a Heal spell.~
@35953     = ~Volcanic Eruption~
@36953     = ~Volcanic Eruption
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 9
Range: Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 12
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell triggers a small volcanic eruption centered on the caster. Multiple balls of lava (one per two caster levels) fly through the area in random directions and hit the ground in random spots. Each ball of lava deals 6d6 fire damage (Reflex save for half) to all creatures within 20 feet of its landing point. The caster is completely unharmed by this spell, but their allies are still in danger.~
@35954     = ~Storm of Vengeance~
@36954     = ~Storm of Vengeance
(Conjuration)
Level: Clr 9, Drd 9, Talos 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 12
Area of Effect: 25-foot radius
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell conjures a divine storm cloud which releases damaging torrents upon creatures in the area of effect. Each round, the nature of the storm is different:

1st round: Fire Storm - Deals 1d6 fire damage per level (max 20d6) with a Reflex save for half.
2nd round: Acid Storm - Deals 3d6 acid damage per round for 1 round per 3 levels (max 24d6 and 8 rounds). A Reflex save halves the number of rounds.
3rd round: Lightning Storm - Deals 12d10 electricity damage with a Reflex save with +4 DC for half.
4th round: Ice Storm - Deals 4d6 bludgeoning damage and 4d6 cold damage with no save.~
@35955     = ~Contingent Resurrection~
@36955     = ~Contingent Resurrection
(Conjuration)
Level: Clr 9
Range: Touch
Duration: 8 hours or until triggered
Casting Time: 18
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell stores a Resurrection spell in the target, which will be triggered the next time the target dies within 8 hours. The target will be brought back to life and will regain all hit points.~
@35956     = ~Tornado~
@36956     = ~Tornado
(Evocation)
Level: Drd 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

A more powerful version of the spell Whirlwind, the spell creates a tornado at the target point that moves randomly. Creatures that come within 15 feet of the tornado get sucked up into it, taking 3d8 slashing damage per second that they stay inside it. Creatures are usually ejected from the tornado after about a round. Huge creatures such as frost giants and dragons aren't sucked up into the tornado but still take damage while in the area of effect. Only one tornado may be active at a time. This spell can only be cast outdoors.~
@35957     = ~Summon Deva~
@36957     = ~Summon Deva
(Conjuration)
Level: Clr 9
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 50 rounds
Casting Time: 12
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell summons an angelic deva to assist the party. The deva has a variety of priest spells, can fly, and wields a mace that forces creatures it hits to make a Fortitude save or be stunned. The party can only summon one deva per 8 hours. This spell may only be cast by good characters.~
@37151     = ~True Strike~
@38151     = ~True Strike
(Divination) 
Level: Brd 1, Pal 1, Rgr 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Caster
Duration: 9 seconds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

The True Strike spell gives the caster incredible insights into his or her enemies' weaknesses, but only for an extremely short duration. For 9 seconds, the caster gains a +20 attack bonus.~
@37152     = ~Reflect Attack~
@38152     = ~Reflect Attack
(Abjuration)
Level: Brd 1, Pal 1, Sor/Wiz 1, Helm 1
Range: Caster
Duration: 8 hours or until triggered
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

After this spell is cast, the next instance of physical damage the caster would receive is reflected back at the attacker, damaging them instead. If the physical damage came from a weapon, any on-hit effects of the weapon will also be reflected back at the attacker.~
@37154     = ~Simple Summoning~
@38154     = ~Simple Summoning
(Conjuration)
Level: Brd 2, Clr 2, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: 1000 ft.
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Simple Summoning summons the target of the spell. The target is instantly teleported to the caster's side. Unlike most other summoning spells, Simple Summoning gives no control over the creature. This spell could either be used to rescue an ally (e.g. if the ally was paralyzed and being attacked by enemies), or to transport an enemy into a vulnerable position. Creatures and objects that are part of a structure (e.g. support beams) are unaffected.

Simple Summoning can be cast on any creature the party sees, even one outside of the caster's visual range.~
@37155     = ~Deathwatch~
@38155     = ~Deathwatch
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 1, Rgr 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Caster
Duration: 10 rounds/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

Deathwatch lets the caster learn precisely how close other creatures are to death. As long as a party member has Deathwatch and isn't incapacitated, if you hover the cursor over an enemy until it displays the tooltip, it will show the enemy's current and maximum Hit Points.~
@37156     = ~Jump~
@38156     = ~Jump
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 1, Rgr 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Touch
Duration: 30 rounds
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell greatly increases the recipient's jump distance, allowing them to jump over obstacles or across large gaps. For the duration, the recipient gains the Jump ability, usable at will. By using this ability, the character jumps to a target point up to 20 feet away.

In addition, while this spell is active, the recipient is immune to falling damage from all sources.~
@37157     = ~Vanish~
@38157     = ~Vanish
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

A lesser version of Invisibility, this spell causes the caster to become invisible for a short time, or until the caster attacks or casts a spell on another creature.

Vanish is less effective for sneaking past groups of enemies, and better suited for getting out of tight spots in combat. Wizard/rogues can use this spell as an easy way to prepare for another sneak attack.~
@37251     = ~Identify Creature~
@38251     = ~Identify Creature
(Divination)
Level: Brd 2, Drd 2, Rgr 2, Sor/Wiz 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Identify Creature reveals useful combat information about the target creature. The information includes the creature's level, current and maximum hit points, number of attacks per round, ability scores, resistances, saving throws, and various other traits that depend on the creature.~
@37252     = ~Sound Burst~
@38252     = ~Sound Burst
(Evocation)
Level: Brd 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: Fortitude partial

This spell releases an extremely loud and jarring burst of sound. Creatures in the area of effect take 1d8 magic damage and must make a Fortitude save or be stunned for 1 round. Deaf creatures are not stunned but still take damage. The caster is unaffected by this spell.~
@37253     = ~Levitate~
@38253     = ~Levitate
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 2, Sor/Wiz 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex negates

This spell suspends the target in the air if it fails a Reflex save (Allies are affected with no saving throw necessary). While levitating, the target cannot move unless it can fly, and it gets a -20 attack penalty with melee weapons, but also gets +20 AC against melee weapons. If cast on an ally, that ally can levitate up and down as well. While the character is selected, hold Left Shift to lift them up or hold Right Shift to pull them down. While at ground level, the character can move and loses the bonuses and penalties, but the spell doesn't end immediately.

When cast on an ally, Levitate lasts 4 rounds. When cast on a non-allied creature, it lasts 10 rounds.~
@37254     = ~Arcane Sight~
@38254     = ~Arcane Sight
(Divination)
Level: Brd 2, Sor/Wiz 2
Range: Caster
Duration: 5 rounds/level
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

Arcane Sight lets the caster see what magical effects are on a creature. While the spell is in effect and the caster isn't incapacitated, if you hover the cursor over a creature and press Tab, a list of all the magical effects on the creature from spells and abilities will be displayed, along with their remaining durations.~
@37255     = ~Enlarge Creature~
@38255     = ~Enlarge Creature
(Transmutation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell causes the target to temporarily grow twice as large in each dimension. The target gains +8 Strength and Constitution; these are size bonuses which stack with other bonuses to these attributes. The target's speed is also increased (since they cover more distance with each stride). However, the target also gets a -4 penalty to Dexterity, AC, and attack rolls due to increased size. The target cannot benefit from invisibility, blur, or mirror image.~
@37256     = ~Darkness~
@38256     = ~Darkness
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 2, Clr 2, Sor/Wiz 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 20-foot radius
Saving Throw: Fortitude negates

This spell creates magical darkness in the area of effect. Creatures without darkvision must make a Fortitude saving throw or be effectively blinded. Creatures with darkvision aren't blinded, but even they have only a limited ability to see through magical darkness, getting a -4 attack penalty on a failed save. Creatures with superior 120 foot darkvision (e.g. drow, gray dwarves or deep gnomes) only get a -2 attack penalty. Devils and creatures immune to blindness are unaffected.~
@37351     = ~Clairvoyance~
@38351     = ~Clairvoyance
(Divination)
Level: Drd 2, Rgr 2
Range: Caster
Duration: Permanent
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: Entire area
Saving Throw: None

The Clairvoyance spell empowers the caster to see in their mind the geographical features and buildings of the region they are currently exploring. It extends to a great range, but cannot reveal creatures or their movements. Clairvoyance can be cast indoors or outdoors.~
@37352     = ~Remove Magic~
@38352     = ~Remove Magic
(Abjuration)
Level: Clr 3, Drd 4, Pal 3, Sor/Wiz 3, Oghma 2
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous 
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius 
Saving Throw: Will negates

Remove Magic is like Dispel Magic, except it only affects enemies. When cast, it dispels most magical effects on enemies in the area of effect who fail a Will save with +5 DC.~
@37353     = ~Throw~
@38353     = ~Throw
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 4, Sor/Wiz 3
Range: Touch
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Reflex half

This spell throws the target into the air with incredible force. The target is knocked back as it is sent hurtling through the air. When it lands or hits the ceiling, it takes bludgeoning damage based on how fast it was moving right before the collision, up to 5d6 plus 1d6 per caster level (max 20d6 total from a level 15 caster). If the target succeeds on a Reflex save, it is thrown with less force and will only take about half damage.~
@37354     = ~Moment of Prescience~
@38354     = ~Moment of Prescience
(Divination)
Level: Brd 3, Drd 4, Sor/Wiz 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

The recipient of this spell can momentarily gain the ability to see into the future, and can see any attack or spell coming. The target gains three abilities, which can be used to give them a +25 bonus to attack, to AC or to saving throws, depending on the ability chosen, for 1 round. Once one of these abilities is used, all three disappear. If not used, the abilities also disappear after 3 hours.

The abilities granted by Moment of Prescience can be used as a free action.~
@37355     = ~Fly~
@38355     = ~Fly
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 3, Rgr 3, Sor/Wiz 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This wondrous spell gives the recipient the power to fly. For the duration, the character can fly over normally impassable gaps and obstacles. In addition, unless the character is fighting in melee or casting a touch spell, they will be flying far enough above the ground that most melee attacks against them will be made at a -20 penalty. The effects of Fly are suppressed as long as the character is indoors.~
@37356     = ~Perception Filter~
@38356     = ~Perception Filter
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 1, Sor/Wiz 1
Range: Touch
Duration: 10 rounds/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

Perception Filter causes the recipient to attract less notice without actually being invisible. Enemies will ignore the character, not attacking or casting spells on them, as long as there is someone else they can target instead (who isn't affected by this spell). If there are no other allies they can target instead, the enemies will notice the character and attack them.

If a character under the effect of this spell attacks or casts a spell, that does not cause the spell to end, but the enemy they are currently targeting can still notice them.~
@37357     = ~Legend Lore~
@38357     = ~Legend Lore
(Divination) 
Level: Brd 3, Oghma 3
Range: Caster
Duration: 10 rounds/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

A more powerful version of the spell Identify, Legend Lore temporarily increases the lore of the caster, allowing them to identify multiple magical items. For the duration, the caster's Knowledge (Arcana) is increased by 30.~
@37358     = ~Project Image~
@38358     = ~Project Image
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 3, Sor/Wiz 3
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates an illusory duplicate of the caster. For the duration, the caster controls this image instead of their body, can see through its eyes, and can command it to attack or cast spells. Spells cast this way use up the caster's spell slots.

Importantly, any damage the image takes will not harm the caster when the spell is over, and any status ailments inflicted on the image will not affect the caster. Thus, this spell can be used to send the image into risky situations that would be unwise to send the actual character into.

While Project Image is active, the character record screen and HP bar record the stats of the image rather than the caster. When the image takes damage or is killed, the HP bar will go down, but the caster will be fine afterwards as long as their body didn't take damage.

The spell ends early if the image is destroyed (it starts with the same HP as the caster), if it's dispelled, if the caster is killed, or if the party moves to another area.~
@37359     = ~Glibness~
@38359     = ~Glibness
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 3
Range: Caster
Duration: 10 rounds/level
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell greatly increases the character's ability to fool others. For the duration, the character's Bluff skill is increased by 30.~
@37451     = ~Teleport Field~
@38451     = ~Teleport Field
(Transmutation) 
Level: Brd 5, Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 15-foot radius
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a strange magical field in the area of effect. Any hostile creature in the field will be teleported to a random location in the field each round.~
@37452     = ~Phantasmal Killer~
@38452     = ~Phantasmal Killer
(Illusion)
Level: Brd 4, Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Will or Fortitude negates

Phantasmal Killer causes the target to be struck down by an embodiment of its worst fears. The target may make a Will save to disbelieve the illusion. On a failure, they must make a Fortitude save or die. Even on a successful Fortitude save, they still take 3d6 magic damage. If the target was panicking when they got hit by this spell, the DC of both saves is increased by 6.~
@37453     = ~Ghoulish Feast~
@38453     = ~Ghoulish Feast
(Necromancy)
Level: Clr 4, Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Caster
Duration: 10 rounds/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: Special

This spell lets the caster summon undead by killing other creatures. During the duration of this spell, whenever the caster kills a creature, a ghoul rises to feast upon the remains. That ghoul will serve the caster for 8 hours. A ghoul will only be summoned if the caster dealt the killing damage to the creature; if the caster damaged the creature but another party member finished it off, the caster will not get a ghoul. The ghouls' paralyzing touch uses the DC of this spell as cast by the caster. Ghoulish Feast cannot be cast by good characters.~
@37454     = ~Copy Spell~
@38454     = ~Copy Spell
(Universal)
Level: Brd 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Permanent until released
Casting Time: Free action
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell copies a spell that another creature is casting, allowing the bard to cast that spell once. Copy Spell should be cast on another creature that is casting a spell. The bard gains a special ability that lets them cast that same spell. Once used, the ability is gone until Copy Spell is cast again. Copy Spell cannot copy innate abilities, nor can it copy spells of a higher spell level than the bard can currently cast. Casting Copy Spell itself is a free action, but casting the copied spell could take some time.~
@37455     = ~Polymorph Self~
@38455     = ~Polymorph Self
(Transmutation)
Level: Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Caster
Duration: 1 minute/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

Polymorph Self allows the caster to assume the form of a creature of moderate power. While in another form, the caster has its Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, base Armor Class, resistances, immunities, attacks, and special abilities. The caster can polymorph into one of the following forms:

* Fomorian Giant (can throw boulders at long range)
* Troll (regenerates 1 HP per second)
* Umber Hulk (nearby enemies must make Will save each round or be confused)
* Wyvern (can fly, and each hit poisons the target on a failed Fortitude save)~
@37456     = ~Imbue with Spell Ability~
@38456     = ~Imbue with Spell Ability
(Universal)
Level: Clr 4, Brd 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 8 hours or until released
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

By casting Imbue with Spell Ability, the caster grants another creature the ability to cast one of the caster's spells once. Immediately after casting this spell, the caster must attempt to cast another spell of any level, which must be an abjuration, conjuration or divination spell. Instead of being cast, that spell is stored in the creature on which Imbue with Spell Ability was just cast (consuming one use of the spell). That creature gains a special ability that lets them cast the spell once. If unused, that ability disappears after 8 hours.~
@37457     = ~Chaos Cast~
@38457     = ~Chaos Cast
(Universal)
Level: Sor/Wiz 4
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Special
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: Special

This spell casts a random wizard spell on the target creature, which could be a spell of any level between 1 and 8. The nature of the spell depends on the target. If the target is an enemy, they will receive a harmful spell, but if the target is an ally, they will receive a beneficial spell. Targeting restrictions are obeyed (a spell that only affects the caster will not be rolled unless the target is the caster).

The main advantage of Chaos Cast is that the random spell is more likely to be higher than level 4 than lower (since there are more levels above level 4 than below). The disadvantage is that the spell might not be useful in the current situation.~
@37551     = ~Steal Spells~
@38551     = ~Steal Spells
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 5, Sor/Wiz 5, Mask 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: Instantaneous
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell steals memorized spells from the target and grants their spell slots to the caster. The caster makes a Pick Pockets roll, adding their caster level (and any normal bonuses to Pick Pockets). For every 10 points of the total roll, the target loses one memorized spell of 5th-level or lower, and the caster regains one spell of 4th-level or lower (prioritizing the highest-level spells that can be lost or regained this way). There is no Saving Throw, though Spell Resistance may prevent the theft.~
@37552     = ~Ghostform~
@38552     = ~Ghostform
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 5, Clr 5, Sor/Wiz 5
Range: Touch
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell turns the recipient incorporeal for a limited period of time. While incorporeal, the character gets damage reduction 5/+1, and they have a 50% chance to ignore any instance of physical damage. They are still tangible enough to attack and cast spells. The recipient can also move through walls while incorporeal. Simply click on a point to move to, and the character will float to that point, bypassing normally impassable obstacles in the way.~
@37553     = ~Rewind Time~
@38553     = ~Rewind Time
(Transmutation)
Level: Brd 5, Sor/Wiz 5
Range: Caster
Duration: -2 rounds
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: Caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell briefly reverses time for the caster, reverting them to the state they were in two rounds ago. The caster's HP is restored to what it was two rounds ago, as is their location in the area. The caster also regains the magical effects they had two rounds ago, while losing effects gained in the past two rounds (including harmful status effects). Rewind Time does not restore memorized spells expended in the last two rounds.~
@37554     = ~Wall of Force~
@38554     = ~Wall of Force
(Abjuration)
Level: Sor/Wiz 5, Selune 5
Range: Sight of Caster
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: 20-foot long, 5-foot wide wall
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates a wall of magical force, which stays for 5 rounds. Creatures cannot pass through the wall, though they can still fly over it, teleport past it, or float through it while incorporeal. The wall cannot be dispelled. Only one Wall of Force can be active at a time.~
@37555     = ~Second Chance~
@38555     = ~Second Chance
(Enchantment)
Level: Brd 5, Clr 6
Range: Touch
Duration: 8 hours or until triggered
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: 1 creature
